bilingual.target: 今天让我们让某人开心。

bilingual.source: How do you get to know someone's name?
bilingual.target: 你如何知道某人的名字？

bilingual.source: Who told someone to take a break from running?
This word refers to the years when someone is young.
bilingual.target: 这个词指的是某人年轻的时候。

bilingual.source: Apostrophes are also used to show us that something belongs to someone.
bilingual.target: 撇号也用于表示某物属于某人。

bilingual.source: She will speak when she loves someone with all her heart.
bilingual.target: 当她全心全意爱上某人时，她就会说话。

bilingual.source: What are you supposed to do when you meet someone for the first time?
bilingual.target: 你第一次见到某人时应该做什么？

bilingual.source: In your country, what are you supposed to do when you meet someone for the first time?
bilingual.target: 在你的国家，当你第一次见到某人时，你应该做什么？

list.abstract: Someone（英 [ˈsʌmwʌn]，美 [ˈsʌmwʌn]），英语单词，作代词为某人；有人；重要的人。例句为Laura, someone is ringing the doorbell.（Laura，有人在按门铃。）
英文单词释义1代词pron. 某人,有人；2名词n.重要人物,有名气的人。Someone是孙燕姿自己作词作曲的歌曲，开始写给郑秀文，歌名是知道的请告诉我，后来由孙燕姿自己演唱并收录进专辑《Start 自选集》。

yingyinNormal.en: I think someone owes me an apology.
yingyinNormal.zh: 某人貌似该给我磕头认错哦。

yingyinNormal.en: She made me baby-proof the whole hotel. Someone's over-protective.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她让我把整个酒店都做防护了，某人过分保护了。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, Name of someone in room. Chandler. Come on, seriously.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，“说出房里某人的名字”。钱德。拜托，正经一点。

yingyinNormal.en: Apparently someone was being awfully flirty while not wearing their engagement ring, causing another someone to show up here thinking the first someone might be available.
yingyinNormal.zh: 貌似某人没有戴订婚戒，而且整天跟人眉来眼去，所以招惹了那人来到这里，因为他以为某人还单身。

yingyinNormal.en: Think about the last time you judged someone based on their behavior, especially a time when you really feel like you changed your mind about someone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想一下你上一次根据他人行为，而评断某人的时候尤其是当你真心觉得，你想改变你对某人印象的时候。

yingyinNormal.en: No, you see, someone was supposed to take them down around New Year's, but obviously someone forgot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，某人在新年期间就应该把它拿下，她显然是忘了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, someone's got a lot of fancy new lab equipment. I know.
yingyinNormal.zh: 某人这里多了好多新的酷炫设备啊。对啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, God. Don't make it so hard on her. Look, the first someone is the deceitful you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别说得这么复杂，某人指的是不忠的你。

yingyinNormal.en: Someone up there likes me. But people down here are pissed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那上头的某人还真喜欢我，但是下面的一些人都气死了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh my God. Oh, you say someone's name enough, they turn around.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的天啊。只要一直念某人的名字，那个人就会转过身来。

yingyinNormal.en: You walked around all night in the city by yourself? He hooked up. He hooked up with someone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你整夜一个人在外面乱晃？他做了，他跟某人做了。

yingyinNormal.en: On one hand, learning very negative, highly immoral information about someone typically has a stronger impact than learning very positive, highly moral information.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一方面，知道关于某人非常负面、非常不道德的信息，基本上会有更强的影响，相对于得知某人有非常正面、道德的信息。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, someone was supposed to write, "Rach, take down the lights" and put it on the refrigerator.
yingyinNormal.zh: 某人应该写个字条“瑞秋, 拿下圣诞灯”然后贴在冰…

yingyinNormal.en: Finish your thought. A part of someone's murder. Jesus. I wanna believe you, Francis.
yingyinNormal.zh: 说完吧。某人的谋杀。天啊。我想要相信你 Francis。

yingyinNormal.en: Precisely, I didn't do anything. Now does someone feel like checking her emotional math?
yingyinNormal.zh: 对啊，我什么都没干啊，某人是不是该仔细想想自己在说啥啊？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, you guys are so lucky you're here with people. I'd love to share this with someone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 喔，你们真幸运，有人陪你们到这里。我真想跟某人分享这一切。

yingyinNormal.en: But you said you were working with me. Someone's got two dates to the nerd prom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但你答应我要跟我一起做我们的项目。某人邀了两妞去参加宅男舞会呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Break time's over. Get your work done. Looks like someone has an issue with anger franagement.
yingyinNormal.zh: 休息时间结束了，去完成工作。看来某人的愤怒"朋理"有些问题啊。

yingyinNormal.en: It was unclear what she was, at least to someone. This was a test. We were difficult to spot then.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不清楚她想干什么，至少对于某人来说。这算是个测试。我们很难查清他们的身份。

yingyinNormal.en: I didn't. Even when I found out, all right, well, let's just say I found something about someone and let's just say she's gonna keep it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，即使我发现…总之我发现了某人的某件事，但是我不会说出来。

examination_example.sentence: They credit their success to having <highlight>someone</highlight> in their life who believes in them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们把自己的成功归功于生活中有人相信他们。

examination_example.sentence: And why would <highlight>someone</highlight> continue to believe a false or inaccurate idea anyway?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 而且为什么会有人继续相信一个错误或不准确的想法呢？

examination_example.sentence: Convincing <highlight>someone</highlight> to change their mind is really the process of convincing them to change their tribe.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 说服别人改变主意其实就是说服他们改变自己的部落。

examination_example.sentence: After all, without counting, how can <highlight>someone</highlight> tell whether there are, say, seven or eight coconuts in a tree?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 毕竟，不去数的话，怎么会有人分辨出树上有七个还是八个椰子？

examination_example.sentence: A man in Halifax, Canada, wanted to find out if people were thankful for <highlight>someone</highlight> holding the door open for them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 加拿大哈利法克斯的一名男子想知道人们是否感谢他们开门的人。

examination_example.sentence: I nearly tripped over <highlight>someone</highlight>'s computer electrical lead the other day in my local café.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 前几天在我当地的咖啡馆里，我差点被别人的电脑电线绊倒。

examination_example.sentence: Be sure you are doing it for yourself, not for <highlight>someone</highlight> else.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 确保你这样做是为了自己，而不是为了某人。

examination_example.sentence: Before you ask <highlight>someone</highlight> for help, find out whether he is the right person for your problem.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在你向某人寻求帮助之前，先弄清楚他是否是解决你问题的合适人选。

examination_example.sentence: It's easy to tell <highlight>someone</highlight> good news, but what about bad news?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 告诉某人好消息很容易，但坏消息呢？
